headline: Mid-America Apartment Communities (MAA) Q3 FFO and Revenues Miss Estimates
summary: Mid-America Apartment Communities (MAA) delivered FFO and revenue surprises of -0.46% and -0.30%, respectively, for the quarter ended September 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Mid-America Apartment Communities: Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The real estate investment trust, based in Germantown, Tennessee, said it had funds from operations of $217.3 million, or $2.16 per share, in the period. The average estimate of eight analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of $2.17 per share. Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry.
